-- Mexico Drug-Related Deaths Fell 6% to 856 in June, Milenio Says
-- B y   J o s e   E n r i q u e   A r r i o j a
-- 2013-07-01T12:29:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-01/mexico-drug-related-deaths-fell-6-to-856-in-june-milenio-says.html
Killings related to drug violence
declined in June from May, Mexico City newspaper Milenio
 reported  today.
* June’s casualties fell to lowest level since Nov. 2011, when
756 people were reported killed in organized crime-related
events, according to data compiled by the daily
* With 345 deaths, states of Chihuahua, Sinaloa and Guerrero
remained Mexico’s most violent last month: Milenio
* # of killings in May was revised to 890 from 902 originally
reported
* Total drug-related deaths since President Enrique Pena Nieto
took office Dec. 1 rose to 6,607, the newspaper said  To contact the reporter on this story:
